<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
European. The species was described from Czech Republic (
<bibRefCitation author="Sevcik, J." journalOrPublisher="Casopis Slezskeho zemskeho muzea, Serie A, Vedy prirodni (Opava)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="97 - 105" title="Fifty species of fungus gnats (Diptera: Mycetophilidae) new for the Czech Republic and / or Slovakia, including a new species of Allodia Winnertz" volume="48" year="1999">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ševčík">Sevcik</normalizedToken>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
), and has been recorded from Sweden (north, south, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kjaerandsen, J." journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="1 - 165" title="Annotated checklist of fungus gnats from Sweden (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Diadocidiidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae)" volume="65" year="2007">Kjaerandsen et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), Russian Karelia (
<bibRefCitation author="Polevoi, A. V." journalOrPublisher="Karelian Research Centre, Russian Academy of Sciences, Petrozavodsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Fungus gnats (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae, Diadocidiidae, Mycetophilidae) in Karelia." year="2000">Polevoi 2000</bibRefCitation>
) and Finland (south). Here reported from North Finland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
Sampling sites are a headwater stream and a swampy lake shore. Immature stages are unknown. Related species 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Allodia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Allodia (Brachycampta) pistillata" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pistillata" subGenus="Brachycampta">Allodia (Brachycampta) pistillata</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lundström">Lundstroem</normalizedToken>
was reared by Jakovlev (
<bibRefCitation author="Jakovlev, J." journalOrPublisher="Karelian Research Center, Russian Academy of Sciences, Forest Research Institute, Petrozavodsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Palaearctic Diptera associated with fungi and myxomycetes" year="1994">Jakovlev 1994</bibRefCitation>
) from the ascomycete fungus 
<taxonomicName class="Pezizomycetes" family="Pezizaceae" genus="Peziza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Peziza" order="Pezizales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Peziza</taxonomicName>
sp.
</paragraph>
